RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 5600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR NEBRASKA-BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEBRASKA RED chased the top pair down the backstretch, moved up three wide in the lane and finished well to get up under strong handling. SEGOVIANA dueled for the early lead from the outside of rival, had a clear lead near the eighth pole but couldn't hold off the winner late to finish second best. TRICKY MOM was forced in tight at the break, lost a considerable amount of ground at the start, advanced towards the leaders through the far turn and made a good late rally while racing four wide to wide. HOT CAVIAR was hustled from the inside, raced three wide between in the drive and had not enough. LOT'SA SILVER dueled for the early lead along the rail and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Tricky Mom
ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight break, closing in, 4-5 wide

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 38. Maiden Claiming Purse 4900. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WANDAS CAFE showed good early foot to cross over an set the early lead along the inside and held gamely to stay clear under steady handling. CHARACTER COUNTS was rated along the inside down the backstretch, angled out four into the lane and got up for the place position. SLOOPY HANG ON was coaxed along early between rivals and raced even with no closing run. MISS GRAND SLAM was slow early, raced five wide into the lane and never threatened. ITHOUGHTIKNEW was forwardly placed from the outside to lay up close three wide and faded.
